  Pages = {479--513},
  Quotes = {For acyclic schemes there are efficient (polynomial-time) algorithms for solving problems that are NP-complete in the unrestricted case. ... \cite{A} collection of sets can be viewed as being a hypergraph.},
  R-Dechter92Chapter = {Acyclic constraint networks (ACNs) ... were first characterized and evaluated in the relational database literature \cite{Beeri83jacm}. ... Several efficient procedures for identifying and finding a representative join tree have been described \cite{Maier83book}. One scheme that proved particularly useful is based on the observation that a CN is acyclic if, and only if, its primal graph is both chordal and conformal \cite{Beeri83jacm}. ... A graph is conformal if each of its maximal cliques corresponds to a constraint in the original CN.},
