  R-Durrantwhyte06Ram = {Work by Smith and Cheesman [this] and Durrant-Whyte [DurrantWhyte88tra] established a statistical basis for describing relationships between landmarks and manipulating geometric uncertainty. A key element of this work was to show that there must be a high degree of correlation between estimates of the location of different landmarks in a map and that indeed these correlations would grow with successive observations.},
